mmentator see david duffield sports commentator david duffield david duffield  born  age – nationality american alma mater cornell university occupation chairman of workday inc net worth us billion june  david duffield born  is an american businessman in the software industry he is the cofounder and former chairman of peoplesoft the cofounder and coceo at workday inc and has been on the forbes worlds richest people list contents  early life  career  peoplesoft  workday  philanthropy and maddies fund  awards  personal life  references  external links early lifeedit duffield received a bachelors degree in electrical engineering and an mba from cornell university and is the benefactor behind duffield hall a nanoscale science or nanotechnology and engineering facility at cornell while at cornell duffield was a member of beta theta pi careeredit duffield established two mainframe application software companies he was ceo chairman and chief product architect at integral systems the first company to offer dbbased human resource and accounting systems he also cofounded information associates which specialized in applications for the higher education market he began his career at ibm as a marketing representative and systems engineer peoplesoftedit duffield founded peoplesoft in  and served as the companys ceo and board chairman peoplesoft grew to be the worlds secondlargest application software company before being acquired by oracle in january  workdayedit in march  duffield and former peoplesoft vice chair and head of product strategy aneel bhusri started workday inc a company that provides financial management and human capital management software delivered in a software as a service saas model the company is headquartered in pleasanton california and employed approximately  people in  with duffield and bhusri serving as coceos at workday duffield is also the companys chief customer advocate philanthropy and maddies fundedit duffield is also known for his philanthropic activities on behalf of animals in  duffield and his wife cheryl established maddies fund originally named the duffield family foundation in january  the board of directors restructured the foundation defined its mission and adopted the current name the organization is named after maddie a miniature schnauzer who was the duffields source of unconditional love and friendship for ten years and a lighthouse during the stormy period of the couples work careers maddie died of cancer in  and duffield acted on his earlier promise to his pet if we ever make some money i promise we will give it back to you and your kind so others can be as happy as we are today the duffields have endowed maddies fund with more than  million and have spent more than  million through fiscal year  to save the lives of dogs and cats the organization believes that the duffields have given more of their personal wealth to the animal welfare cause than any other individuals and although they dont want to make a big fuss over their unprecedented contribution they do want to honor their cherished companion and the special bond they shared with her in may  the duffields put their  acre estate in california on the market as they decided to move back to their home in tahoe the asking price for the property was  million with the proceeds of the sale going towards maddies fund awardsedit  ey entrepreneur of the year award recipient personal lifeedit david duffield is married to cheryl duffield between  and  they lived in alamo california but now live near lake tahoe referencesedit  httpwwwforbescomprofiledavidduffieldlistbillionaires  httpwwwduffieldcornelledu  httpmoneycnncomtechnologyoraclepeoplesoft  httpwwwbizjournalscomsanfranciscoprinteditionworkdaysteepgrowthcurvetonearlyhtml  httpwwwworkdaycomcompanyleadershipteamdaveduffieldphp  a b c maddies fund  annual report p   a b c d about maddie maddies fund accessed sept    tilton sarah dog heaven david duffields large bay area estate seeks  million   dav