lications for the higher education market he began his career at ibm as a marketing representative and systems engineer peoplesoftedit duffield founded peoplesoft in  and served as the companys ceo and board chairman peoplesoft grew to be the worlds secondlargest application software company before being acquired by oracle in january  workdayedit in march  duffield and former peoplesoft vice chair and head of product strategy aneel bhusri started workday inc a company that provides financial management and human capital management software delivered in a software as a service saas model the company is headquartered in pleasanton california and employed approximately  people in  with duffield and bhusri serving as coceos at workday duffield is also the companys chief customer advocate philanthropy and maddies fundedit duffield is also known for his philanthropic activities on behalf of animals in  duffield and his wife cheryl established maddies fund originally named the duffield family foundation in january  the board of directors restructured the foundation defined its mission and adopted the current name the organization is named after maddie a miniature schnauzer who was the duffields source of unconditional love and friendship for ten years and a lighthouse during the stormy period of the couples work careers maddie died of cancer in  and duffield acted on his earlier promise to his pet if we ever make some money i promise we will give it back to you and your kind so others can be as happy as we are today the duffields have endowed maddies fund with more than  million and have spent more than  million through fiscal year  to save the lives of dogs and cats the organization believes that the duffields have given more of their personal wealth to the animal welfare cause than any other individuals and although they dont want to make a big fuss over their unprecedented contribution they do want to honor their cherished companion and the special bond they shared with her in may  the duffields put their  acre estate in california on the market as they decided to move back to their home in tahoe the asking price for the property was  million with the proceeds of the sale going towards maddies fund awardsedit  ey entrepreneur of the year award recipient personal lifeedit david duffield is married to cheryl duffield between  and  they lived in alamo california but now live near lake tahoe referencesedit  httpwwwforbescomprofiledavidduffieldlistbillionaires  httpwwwduffieldcornelledu  httpmoneycnncomtechnologyoraclepeoplesoft  httpwwwbizjournalscomsanfranciscoprinteditionworkdaysteepgrowthcurvetonearlyhtml  httpwwwworkdaycomcompanyleadershipteamdaveduffieldphp  a b c maddies fund  annual report p   a b c d about maddie maddies fund accessed sept    tilton sarah dog heaven david duffields large bay area estate seeks  million   dave duffield of peoplesoft named entrepreneur of the yearthe free library  business wire april    dog heaven david duffields large bay area estate seeks  million retrieved  external linksedit workday web site retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitledavidduffieldoldid categories  birthsliving peoplesamuel curtis johnson graduate school of management alumnipeople from hohokus new jerseyamerican billionairesamerican technology chief executivescornell university college of engineering alumnipeople from alamo californiahidden categories articles with hcards navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages add links this page was last edited o